text: The Torres Strait Islands are a group of at least 274 small islands in the Torres Strait. Most of the islands are part of the state of Queensland, Australia. A small number are part of Papua New Guinea. The indigenous people of the islands are Torres Strait Islanders. In 2011, the population was 4,248. The island with the most people is Thursday Island. ==References== Category:Islands of Oceania Category:Islands of Australia Category:Melanesia Category:Geography of Papua New Guinea Category:Geography of Queensland Category:Indigenous Australian communities
